  "doc_id": "25690",
  "text": "This sample of 19 adolescents with mild-moderate intellectual disability showed suicidality characteristics similar to adolescents without intellectual disability, which disputes the earlier assumptions [CITATION_1] of intellectual disability serving as a \"buffer\" against suicidal behavior in this population. There was a high prevalence of physical or sexual abuse of the adolescent with intellectual disability prior to hospitalization, which could be the trigger of suicidal behavior also seen in the general population. Another earlier study [CITATION_2] found that 39% of multihandicapped children admitted to a psychiatric hospital were reportedly abused prior to the hospitalization.",
